The Big Alternative Scroller        
Instructions

OVERVIEW

Welcome to the Big Alternative Scroller (BAS).  With BAS you have a
self-contained Titling programme on one (1) disk.  The software
enables you to type in credits, display info, etc. and scroll them
either vertically or horizontally on your monitor screen and likewise
onto video tape.


There are up to 20 fonts of differing styles and sizes which should
suit most applications of the programme.  Up to 4 colours can be
defined from 4096 and utilised as backgrounds, text shades and drop
shadows.  Spacing of words and letters can be achieved easily and all
information including font style, colours scroll speed, etc. can be
saved as a file on disk and easily recalled anytime for further
editing or changes.

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

The Big Alternative Scroller requires an Amiga computer with a minimum
of 1 megabyte of RAM and should work on Version 1.2, 1.3 and 2.0 of
Kickstart.  Only one disk drive is required.  The software does not
require Workbench or any other proprietary programme in order to
operate.  Because the programme runs under its own code and not Amiga
Dos you will not be able to multitask with any other software.  BAS
has been tested on A500's with ram expansions and hard drives - also
A/B2000 machines with 68020 and 68030 based accelerator cards.
Optional requirements are a genlock for video use and a mug of tea.


